OL,7,F"People on the outside perhaps don't
OL,8,Ffully understand that even parties who
OL,9,Fwere diametrically opposed on a whole
OL,10,Frange of issues, they can actually
OL,11,Fwork together quite well behind the
OL,12,Fscenes, but there was a discernible
OL,13,Fchill after that.
OL,15,F"Business was still transacted...
OL,16,Fissues were still brought to the
OL,17,FExecutive, discussions still took
OL,18,Fplace, decisions were taken. I don't
OL,19,Frecall that that became any more
OL,20,Fdifficult than it had been."
