OL,7,FHe added: "It was a protracted
OL,8,Fdiscussion, people had got into fixed
OL,9,Fpositions, it had split along
OL,10,FNationalist/Unionist lines.
OL,12,F"My frustration, as expressed in a
OL,13,Fmessage that night, was born of a
OL,14,Fconcern that this might be how things
OL,15,Fplayed out from here.
OL,17,F"Now, there were difficulties on
OL,18,Foccasion afterward but by and large
OL,19,Fnot of that magnitude."
